drivers competing in 2010. On occasions, a third car was run with a \"guest\" driver.\n\nArgentinian team [[Munchi's Ford World Rally Team]] also entrusts the preparation and running of its car to M-Sport.<ref name=mcp/> The driver running for the team in the 2010 WRC season was [[Federico Villagra]].\n\nFor the 2010 season, M-Sport ran a Ford Focus RS WRC 08 for [[Ken Block (rally driver)|Ken Block]] on behalf of the [[Monster World Rally Team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.monsterworldrallyteam.com/blogs |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-02-15 |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100214153624/http://www.monsterworldrallyteam.com/blogs |archivedate=14 February 2010 |df= }} monster world rally team.com/blogs</ref>\n\n===Ford Fiesta S2000===\nAt the beginning of 2009 Ford with M-Sport started work on a [[Super 2000|S2000]] rally version of the new [[Ford Fiesta]]. The new car, designed by Christian Loriaux, was launched on 18 November 2009 at M-Sport's headquarters. The car will made its public debut as a course car at the [[Rally Scotland|IRC Rally Scotland]] driven by [[Matthew Wilson]]. Ford did not run a works entry in the 2010 [[Intercontinental Rally Challenge|IRC]] but M-Sport did its own programme of events with Ford's support both on the technical and financial side.<ref>[http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/80180 Ford rules out works IRC entry] Autosport website 17 November 2009. Retrieved 19 November 2009</ref> M-Sport announced on 8 January 2010 that it was entering the IRC which means that Ford will be a registered manufacturer in the series.<ref>[http://www.ircseries.com/html/readNews.asp?id=1431 M-Sport joins the Intercontinental Rally Challenge] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713055419/http://www.ircseries.com/html/readNews.asp?id=1431 |date=13 July 2011 }} IRC Website 2010-01-08 Retrieved 2010-01-09</ref> Works Ford WRC driver [[Mikko Hirvonen]] gave the car its first competitive outing on the [[2010 Monte Carlo Rally|Monte Carlo Rally]] leading the event from start to finish.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ircseries.com/html/readNews.asp?id=1496 |title=Monte triumph delights Hirvonen |work=ircseries.com |publisher=[[Intercontinental Rally Challenge]] |accessdate=26 October 2010 |date=23 January 2010 |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723190016/http://www.ircseries.com/html/readNews.asp?id=1496 |archivedate=23 July 2011 |df= }}</ref>\n\nA number of private entry were made in the 2010 [[Super 2000 World Rally Championship]].\n\n===Other series===\n[[File:Ford Fiesta Rally car.JPG|thumb|250px|FSTi rally car at Rally Japan]]\nThe company also runs the one-make [[Ford Fiesta|Fiesta]] Sporting Trophy rally series, which it launched in 2006, and the Fiesta Sporting Trophy International (FSTi) series.<ref name=mcp/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiestasportingtrophy.com/ |title= Ford Fiesta Sporting Trophy |publisher=Fiestasportingtrophy.com |date= |accessdate=27 November 2011}}</ref><ref>[http://www.fiestasportingtrophy.com/aboutFST.asp#downloads :: Ford Fiesta Sporting Trophy ::] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080201154726/http://www.fiestasportingtrophy.com/aboutFST.asp#downloads |date=1 February 2008 }}</ref>\n\nM-Sport started preparing [[Bentley Continental GT|Bentley Continental GT3]] for [[2014 Blancpain Endurance Series season|Blancpain Endurance Series]] and [[2014 British GT season|British GT Championship]] in 2014.\n\nM-Sport supplies [[Ford Fiesta]] Rallycross Supercars to [[Global Rallycross Championship]] teams [[Hoonigan Racing Division]] since 2013, and [[Chip Ganassi Racing]] and [[Bryan Herta Autosport]] since 2015.\n\nM-Sport, alongside Ford Performance and [[Hoonigan Racing Division]] has developed Ford Focus RS RX, scheduled to competing in [[2016 FIA World Rallycross Championship]].\n\n==Racing record==\n\n===Complete WRC results===\n{{main|M-Sport World Rally Team}}\n\n===Complete Blancpain Endur